---
By: Leo Tolstoy
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 258
    Verse: 1
Tags:
  - Hypocrisy
---
Hypocrisy in anything whatever may deceive the cleverest and most penetrating
man, but the least wide-awake of children recognizes it, and is revolted
by it, however ingeniously it may be disguised.
